I. The Nature of the Deception
The Puppet Show: The world is a theatrical stage where individuals play "Mascot" roles (Leader, Elder, Child) out of compulsion, unaware of the strings attached to their limbs.

The Mechanical Beast: The "Chitti" (robotic) city and global systems act as an automated puppeteer, consuming the "Common Good" to fuel its own growth through "Hidden Agendas".

The Sensory Strings: Our five senses are the physical wires the system uses to maintain Moha (attachment) and Sammoha (delusion).

II. The Internal Cremation Ground
The Mind as Smashana: The individual must turn their mind into a burial ground for selfish desires and "Self-Made Scripts".

Burying the Hero: We must stop projecting power onto external "Heroes" or "Saviors"—whether dead, living, or future—and realize that we must save ourselves from our own delusions.

God as Consciousness: The Divine Orchestrator is not an external director but the very consciousness within each being.

III. The Path of the Conscious Cog
Merging with the Good: True liberation is found by merging individual consciousness into the "Common Good" of the Family, Village, City, Country, and World.

The Well-Oiled Machine: By acting with Divine Intent instead of selfish profit, we transform the chaotic "Samsara" into a harmonious, well-oiled machine aligned with the Source of Creation.

IV. The Ultimate End
Dissolution over Death: Death alone does not stop the drama; it only leads to a "Recasting" into a new body or planet to settle unfinished scripts.

Elemental Merger: Only when the inner desires are cremated can the soul merge with the cosmic elements upon death, ending the "Endless Series" of Punarapi Jananam (rebirth).

A Message for Future Generations
"To those who find this in any Yuga: You are not the mask you wear. The strings you feel are only as strong as your desires. Burn the script, bury the hero, and merge your heart with the common welfare. Only then does the actor become the Light."
